cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about unsupervised depth learning from videos, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a dual networks architecture and a self-assembled attention module, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The task of depth estimation from videos can also be related to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM), so these two sub-categories are also possible.
